cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS 

This paper deals with the issue of low-precision representation of deep neural networks, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed solution involves compensating for the quantization-induced shift, which is a technique that falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of iterative evaluation and short training phases, which are techniques that are commonly used in data science (cs.DS).
